.START 

OLYMPIA & YORK DEVELOPMENTS Ltd. has agreed to help arrange an $800 million loan to Campeau Corp. to help the company repurchase junk-bond securities issued by its Federated Department Stores and Allied Stores units.
The loan is separate from a financing that Campeau is seeking to pay off an $800 million bridge loan made by Citibank and which is due April 1990. 

(See: "Campeau's Emergency Loan Agreement Could Set Off Battle With Bondholders" -- WSJ Sept. 22, 1989) 

